properties.name: text
properties.value: Stopping to read any books you find is a good idea - they will contain important information about the world, or may even teach you new abilities. These first few books will explain the controls. Press 'W' to jump. Jumping while airbourne costs mana - it is a spell after all.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Ledge too high? Cast a teleport spell! Click and hold to charge the spell, and release to cast the spell. Remember, spell orbs are effected by gravity and you will teleport to the first solid surface the spell hits.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Welcome to the training course. You will be guided through the abilities you have at your disposal to traverse the Monuments of the Old Gods and bring back their lost knowledge. When you reach the end you will be granted full membership of the Guild of Explorers - pull the lever to open the door and begin!

properties.name: text
properties.value: Multiple levers can effect the same platform in different ways. Some levers can also effect multiple platforms. Your path may be blocked until you activate the correct combination of levers.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Finding it hard to get a good aim for your teleport cast? Do not forget that you have the ability to control the spell orb while it is in the air. Just try moving as if you were the orb.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Bars or grating preventing you from continuing? If you aim carefully it is possible to cast the spell through the obstacle and teleport to the other side. Your teleport spell will pass through these cages without being effected or teleporting you until it hits something more solid.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Levers to open doors are not always directly next to the door they control. Sometimes you will have to explore other rooms to find the correct lever. We have not yet found a limit to have far away they can be, but often they are not too far off.

properties.name: text
properties.value: If the teleport spell will bounce off of walls while you're inside a cage and the spell will not end. You can use this to your advantage to navigate through tight passage ways.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Another spell you should know is the bubble spell. Press 'E' to cycle through your available spells, and select the bubble spell and cast in the same manner as teleport. As the name suggests, bubble creates a large bubble that you can project away from you. The bubble is a physical object, and although it can stay afloat under it's own weight, it will slowly sink if you step on it. You should have enough time to use it as a temporary stepping stone.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Levers and switches can be found in some awkward places within the monuments. Our best engineers still have not been able to determine how the Old Gods were able to build mechanisms that, even all centuries later, barely need a flick of the wrist to activate. But you still cannot interact with something mid teleport.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Inspector's Report #139. Some joker has removed the lever needed to get to the exit. We must find and punish this fool, we must remind the students that it is dangerous to mess with this technology. Also, make sure not to let anyone else take the test until we fix this!

properties.name: text
properties.value: Hahaha that Prof Durato is gonna be mad angry when he finds what ive done! i can just picture his face glowing red right now oh man. dont trip on that first step now...

properties.name: text
properties.value: It only takes one hand to hold your staff while charging your spells. This allows you to pre-aim a spell if you need to dash after pulling a lever.

properties.name: text
properties.value: Want some aiming advice? You often do not need to fully charge a bubble spell - if you fully charge the spell you may not be able to teleport onto it! Try to avoid bouncing it off of walls as well - it will spin if you do. And to get onto a bubble? Try casting teleport straight up next to it, then tap 'A' or 'D' to move onto the bubble.
